Privacy Policy for BacHelper

BacHelper ("the App") is an educational application designed to help students prepare for exams using study sessions, Pomodoro timers, reminders, lessons, and educational videos.

1. Information We Collect

BacHelper does not collect or request personal information such as emails, or phone numbers.

The app stores the following data locally on the user's device only:

name of user and his study division 

Study sessions and schedules

Pomodoro session progress

Completed lessons and subject progress

This data is stored using local device storage (SharedPreferences) and is never transmitted to BacHelper servers.

2. Permissions Used and Their Purpose

BacHelper requests the following permissions strictly for core app functionality:

INTERNET
Used to load educational YouTube videos and display in-app advertisements.

POST_NOTIFICATIONS
Used to send study reminders and scheduled learning notifications.

VIBRATE
Used to enhance notification alerts.

WAKE_LOCK
Used to keep the screen active during Pomodoro study sessions and prevent interruption while studying.

SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM / USE_EXACT_ALARM
Used to deliver precise and time-sensitive study reminders, ensuring notifications occur at the exact scheduled time chosen by the user.

These permissions are never used for tracking, profiling, or background surveillance.

3. Advertising & Third-Party Services

BacHelper displays advertisements using Google AdMob.

Google AdMob may collect limited device information (such as Advertising ID) in accordance with Googleâ€™s Privacy Policy.
BacHelper does not access or store this data.

The app also uses:

YouTube Player API to display educational content.

YouTube may collect data according to its own Privacy Policy.

4. Data Security

All study data remains on the userâ€™s device.
BacHelper does not operate its own servers and does not sell or share user data.

5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

BacHelper is intended for students and does not knowingly collect personal data from children.

